    <PrimAttribute name="scaleFactor" id="459b779e-ad8b-4e19-b333-295e5c03e8b7">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <access>protected</access>
        <text>
This is used to specify how many times wider the item is in comparison
to a standard item.  Most items will have a scaleFactor of 1.
A scaleFactor of 0 is the maximum width possible when displaying the
item.

For example:
If an item is to be displayed in a table and the width of the item
is greater than one column width the scaleFactor would be set to 2
and when displayed the item would be displayed over 2 merged cells.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="text" id="1820dc45-f06c-44fb-bb2f-159b4b0444f8">
        <type name="String"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="type" id="9d882f38-cace-42ff-bcba-14f55d6c70c8">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <access>protected</access>
        <text>
DC_Data = 3
DC_Header = 1
DC_IconLabel = 5
DC_Label = 2
DC_LabelHeader = 7
DC_MoreInfo = 4
DC_Warning  8
</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
